SPDXID: SPDXRef-item20898515
FileChecksum: SHA1: 2dd71a7f01d62c29718a9942837fd02584e4e3d0
FileChecksum: SHA256: 97ac9edddf41000e98f0283e56bf8d21163434941b3abd100cc6b421f56b87db
FileChecksum: MD5: 3b2816651a688eec9643a28dc8c67731
LicenseConcluded: LicenseRef-MIT-54575e81a786e9aa7d98337ec2e1ebb0 AND LicenseRef-Public-domain
LicenseComments: <text> The information in the file is:
Copyright (c) 2015-2016 the fiat-crypto authors (see the AUTHORS file).
Followd by the Text of the MIT license and the following statement: 
Some of this code is taken from the ref10 version of Ed25519 in SUPERCOP
20141124 (http://bench.cr.yp.to/supercop.html). That code is released as
public domain but parts have been replaced with code generated by Fiat
(https://github.com/mit-plv/fiat-crypto), which is MIT licensed.
We checked the Repo and 2016 was one commit, the initial commit (Nov 2016) the initial commit was licensed under MIT with exactly the same text as the above text.
Therefore we concluded MIT AND Public-domain </text>
